===========================================================================
                        GENERAL DESCRIPTION
===========================================================================

This directory containts the denotational semantics of MiniC, a
sub-set of the C language. This sub-set is sufficiently large to
contain any program generated by lustre2C.

The denotation function describing the semantics of a MiniC program
actually provides an interpreter for the program.

===========================================================================
                              CONTENTS
===========================================================================
* DIRECTORY   : CAbstractSyntax.v
  DESCRIPTION : The abstract syntax of MiniC programs.

* DIRECTORY   : BasicTypes.v
  DESCRIPTION : The universe of values that a MiniC expressions may denote.

* DIRECTORY   : Memory.v
  DESCRIPTION : Axiomatization of a computer memory. It also contains
                the type of all the exceptions that may be raisen by 
                the interpreter of MiniC. 

* DIRECTORY   : Stack.v
  DESCRIPTION : Modelization of the stack of temporary variables of
                the MiniC interpretation machine.

* DIRECTORY   : State.v
  DESCRIPTION : The interpretation domains for the different syntactical
                constructions of MiniC.

* DIRECTORY   : CSemantics.v
  DESCRIPTION : Denotational semantics of MiniC.
===========================================================================

* DIRECTORY   : test.c, test1.c, test2.c
  DESCRIPTION : Some tests done on the gcc compiler of C in order to
                precise the semantics of some C instructions
               (evaluation order, address arithmetics, etc.) 
===========================================================================
